were based on previous rulings and applied consistently across the country, in theory at least.

00:08:19.325 --> 00:08:26.455
This was a big step forward, and it marked a shift from community-based justice to one

00:08:26.465 --> 00:08:32.555
where the state, represented by the king, had a central role in defining and enforcing laws.

00:08:33.555 --> 00:08:38.545
Another important development during this time was the introduction of trial

00:08:38.555 --> 00:08:43.770
by jury, of a collection of people deciding the guilt or innocence of an

00:08:43.770 --> 00:08:49.040
individual, rather than a single magistrate or leaving it up to the will of God.

00:08:50.270 --> 00:08:55.930
Now, perhaps you live in a country where the judicial system involves juries.

00:08:56.340 --> 00:08:59.200
Perhaps you have even been on a jury yourself.

00:09:00.010 --> 00:09:05.670
But this early version of a jury wasn’t quite like the one we know today.

00:09:06.248 --> 00:09:11.674
It wasn’t a group of randomly chosen impartial citizens weighing up evidence.

00:09:12.554 --> 00:09:19.194
Instead, it was typically made up of local people who knew the accused person and

00:09:19.354 --> 00:09:25.334
were asked to give their opinion on whether the person was guilty or not, often based

00:09:25.344 --> 00:09:30.234
on their character and what people thought they could have done, rather than coming

00:09:30.234 --> 00:09:34.734
to a conclusion solely based on the evidence of their involvement in the crime.

00:09:35.824 --> 00:09:42.114
And on that note, to state the obvious, proving undeniably that someone committed

00:09:42.114 --> 00:09:47.584
a crime was an awful lot harder in the 11th century compared to the 21st century.

00:09:48.334 --> 00:09:52.484
